So I'm currently using simple-react in a server application that has some long lived queues that process millions of objects a day. For the most part it works great but I have noticed that over time it consumes more and more memory at the rate of about ~8mb an hour.

After some analysis i found that memory is being held through the sizeSignal member of the queue class which has a LinkedBlockingQueue that grows and grows ....

The following code demonstrates the leak:

```
public class QueueTest {
    static class BigObject {
        public final byte[] data = new byte[1_000];
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Queue<BigObject> queue = new Queue<>(new ArrayBlockingQueue<>(100));
        Thread producer = new Thread(()->{
             while (true){
                queue.add(new BigObject());
            }
        });
        producer.start();
        queue.stream().forEach(o->{
            System.out.println(o.toString());
        });
    }
}
```

